# REFACTORING-D — Bulkhead user-guide strategy-dependent markers

A documentation-only polish step. The bulkhead user guide makes several
statements that are silently strategy-dependent (only true for
semaphore, the original default). Adding a "Strategy" column to the
Configuration Reference and Presets tables, plus a one-paragraph header
note establishing the convention, makes the question
"does this apply to all strategies?" answerable from the formatting
alone.

This refactor is **trigger-deferred**. The TODO entry's own
"When to address" clause names the trigger:

> When the library moves out of pre-alpha and gains its first external
> users, or when other pattern user guides (Circuit Breaker, Retry,
> Time Limiter) reach a similar shape and the convention should be
> established consistently across all of them. Whichever comes first.

Until either trigger fires, this document exists as a placeholder so
the work is not forgotten and the chosen approach (Option C from the
TODO entry's review) is recorded. **No work begins on this refactor
until the maintainer confirms the trigger has fired.**

## What this refactor does NOT do

- Does **not** rewrite sections that are universally true. Those gain
  no marker — the convention is "marked = strategy-varying, unmarked =
  universal", and adding markers to universal sections defeats it.
- Does **not** re-order the user guide. Option B from the review
  (Strategies chapter first) was rejected.
- Does **not** scatter strategy hints without the header convention.
  Option A was rejected for the same reason.
- Does **not** touch any code, any test, any ADR.

